How to connect to ZeroNet while at a school, university, workplace, etc. (WINDOWS) (I wish running ZeroNet through Tor was easier.): 

Install Torifier (http://www.torifier.com/), configure the Tor Browser Bundle accordingly and connect (then close Tor), then copy your torrc file from the Tor Browser Bundle (*\Tor Browser\Browser\TorBrowser\Data\Tor\torrc) here: %AppData%/Local/Torifier/torrc, restart Torifier, start Torifier and wait for it to connect, then add /ZeroBundle/Python/Python.exe (and all the other .exes in the folder). There, ZeroNet should now be able to connect while at a school, university, workplace, etc. :D

Warnings: 
---
- Torifier is only a 30 day trial. If you can find an application that does the same thing and is free, please tell me. Thanks!
- You will need to edit the torrc file that you copied from the Tor Browser Bundle so that the directories are correct.

1_19mfoBRfUNYUhv9MAeihggMTW6ejWcctJi.body:
I have found a temporary solution to my issue (Though I would prefer if running ZeroNet through Tor was easier.): 

Install Torifier (http://www.torifier.com/), configure the Tor Browser Bundle accordingly and connect (then close Tor), then copy your torrc file from the Tor Browser Bundle (*\Tor Browser\Browser\TorBrowser\Data\Tor\torrc) here: %AppData%/Local/Torifier/torrc, restart Torifier, start Torifier and wait for it to connect, then add /ZeroBundle/Python/Python.exe (and all the other .exes in the folder). There, ZeroNet should now be able to connect while at a school, university, workplace, etc. :D

Warnings:

Why should I use it?
---
ZeroNet is decentralized so it is extremely hard, if not impossible for governments, companies, etc. to censor content as there is no central server because we are all hosting it. Websites on ZeroNet also cannot be DDOSSed for the same reason. ZeroNet is here to help keep our digital culture alive and uncensored forever.
